SAFRICA ' S HL & H CUTS BACK HEAD OFFICE ROLE . South Africa ' s food and timber holding group Hunt Leuchars & Hepburn Holdings Ltd said on Friday that it was cutting the role of its corporate office following the retirement of group chief executive Neil Morris at the end of March . The firm said that the responsibility for group operations would now reside principally with the individual units ' boards . The group board will now play a monitoring role and the corporate office will be focused on administration under the management of Brian de Klerk . - - Johannesburg newsroom + 27 11 482 1003 
